body:
Thanks, I was looking for the rationale for preventDefault but couldn't find it. I do in fact already use `user-select: none` on the zoomable elements for other reasons.

FWIW, I've also encountered the iframe "stuck drag" problem, and worked around it with an addition to the mousemove handler:

```
      if (d3.event.which === 0) {
        mouseup();
        return;
      }
```

I've patched iD's copy of d3.js to remove the preventDefault so I'll check if I can remove this.
